<br>
Probably their biggest PR mistake is promising a level of customer service that they will likely never attain. If they spend enough money and effort to attain the level of service people were crowing about, they won't be making a profit. Sure, it was great for initial sales, but it's a big problem right about now as people get disillusioned.<br>
<br>
Another thing that really got me was when they said that implementing houses and horses was more important than fixing basic interface issues.<br>
<br>
And that Dave Rickey guy might be a decent designer, but he's got an abrasive personality and throws out nasty one-liners. He's doing as much damage as good talking to the public.<br>
<br>
And most telling of all are which issues they publicly ignore...and I'm not counting trolls, only real issues.<br>
<br>
Don't let me discourage anyone -- I've just found a different way to entertain myself. I think DAoC will survive with a significant following, but it's never gonna be as big as EQ is now. <p>Raski Yzarc (Angelic Few) -- 52 Iksar Monk -- Quellious</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ugarouin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garouin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/16/01 9:30:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: R.I.P. EverQuest</span><hr size=1> Wow.. you've spent more time checking out the game than I have and I play it.<br>
